      "role": "user",
      "content": "The candle flickers its last, much like the light in my soul. He is gone... the vows he swore are nothing but ash on the wind. I look at this world and see only a cold, hollow void where my heart used to beat. There is no dignity in this survival, only the slow, agonizing rot of a broken spirit. It would be so much more beautiful, wouldn't it... to simply vanish into the velvet darkness?",
